Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1%unit}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1%unit} crosswise into strips.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with ¼ tsp @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (add up to ½ tsp if you like; you'll use more later). Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, place @butter{2%tablespoon} and ¼ tsp garlic powder (add more if desired) in a second small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave until just softened, ~{10%seconds}. Season with salt and pepper; stir to combine.

> TIP: Do so in 5-second intervals, checking in between, to avoid melting.

Slice @demi-baguette{2%unit} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through; spread garlic butter onto cut sides. Place cut sides up on a second baking sheet. Toast on middle rack of oven until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and season with @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in @beef stock concentrate{1%unit} and 2 TBSP water. Season with salt and pepper.

Return veggies to pan; stir to combine.

Spread bottom halves of garlic buns with half the garlic mayo. Top with beef and veggie mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{½%cup}.

Return to oven until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}. Drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired.

Divide melts and potatoes between plates. Serve with remaining garlic mayo on the side.